DNA_gyraseA_C,DNA_topoisoIV A type II topoisomerase that negatively supercoils closed circular double-stranded (ds) DNA in an ATP-dependent manner to modulate DNA topology and maintain chromosomes in an underwound state. Also able to catalyze the interconversion of other topological isomers of dsDNA rings, including catenanes and knotted rings.
